- Stay calm & talk to someone you trust.  
- Hang up or ignore messages. DO NOT click links.  
- Protect your money & personal info scammers demand hard-to-trace payments.

SCAM ALERT: Smishing Scam Targeting PA Turnpike Travelers!
 
Scammers are impersonating the Pennsylvania Turnpike and EZ Pass in a new smishing scam, sending fake texts and emails claiming you owe unpaid tolls. DO NOT click on any links or provide any personal information in unsolicited texts or emails claiming to be from the PA Turnpike or EZ Pass. 
 
Protect yourself by:
✅ Only checking your toll accounts through the official PA Turnpike website, EZ Pass website, or PA Toll Pay app. 
✅ Never share personal or payment information with unknown sources.

Our office received calls today concerning the recent OMB guidance. I understand many people are confused about which programs will be affected, so I would like to share information our office has received pertaining to the guidance.
 
- This pause does not apply to any program that provides direct benefit to the American people, including but not limited to: SNAP, Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid, etc.
- Funds for small businesses, farmers, Pell grants, Head Start, rental assistance and other similar programs will not be paused.
- This pause was designed to give agencies time to ensure programs are being executed and government funding is spent in accordance with the President’s policies.
 
My office will continue to monitor for any new information pertaining to this and provide updates to the people of PA08.
